{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7269cedd-1c85-4fef-ac7b-a8528f30ef59","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant (org) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your installed SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2789aea0-f85d-433c-88ab-5ac3f7068fed","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at the environment context, this is a general question about creating a web API project with authentication. The user is likely asking about .NET templates since the repository seems to be .NET-related (mentions NuGet, .NET, MSBuild in the custom instructions).\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of .NET web API templates and authentication options, since this is a general knowledge question rather than a code task.","outputTokens":436,"requestId":"782F:3EF0C4:714732B:7D97381:69F3FA01"},"id":"de8b96f5-fa55-4d4c-88f9